      "content": "hey i have this debate competition coming up for my history class. the topic is about urban development in the 20th century and one of the sides is arguing the \"benefits\" or the logic behind redlining and why certain communities were kept separate. i need to play the opposing side so i need to understand their strongest points. can u help me walk through the most common arguments used to justify redlining back then? like what was the actual reasoning they used to defend it? i need to know what i'm up against.",
