      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay i get that they used \"financial risk\" as a cover, but for my debate i need to actually construct the arguments themselves. like, if i'm the one arguing for the policy, i can't just say \"it was because of racism.\" i need to present it as if it were a logical, economic necessity for the time.\n\nhow would a proponent at the time argue that separating neighborhoods actually protected the overall economy or helped maintain community stability? can you give me a few points that sound like they're coming from a professional urban planner or banker from that era? i need to make the argument sound as \"rational\" and \"objective\" as possible so i can learn how to counter it.",
